
[1]desecrate

   DESECRATE, v.t. [L. To consecrate, from sacred.]

   1. To divert from a sacred purpose or appropriation; opposed to
   consecrate; as, to desecrate a donation to a church.

   2. To divest of a sacred character or office.

   The clergy-cannot suffer corporal punishment, without being previously
   desecrated.
